Description:
Timeless Elegance
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST closing 17th October 2017 UNLESS SOLD PRIOR
A long sweeping driveway creates the perfect entrance to this stunning architect designed residence of timeless appeal situated on an amazing 2475sqm approx allotment set amongst lush landscaped gardens. Situated in a tightly held pocket, the home would be perfect for permanent or holiday living with only minutes walk to the pristine north facing Red Rocks beach.
The immaculately presented home comprises spacious light filled formal and informal living areas, a stylish kitchen and superb attention to detail throughout including beautiful built in cabinetry, raked ceilings, quality fixtures and fittings and plenty of storage. The central formal living area boasts a warm and inviting open fireplace creating the perfect ambience on those cold winter evenings with a large sliding door leading out to an expansive north facing outdoor entertaining deck. Large windows throughout the comfortable home take in wonderful and picturesque views of the stunning garden. The main lower level of the home comprises three good size bedrooms including the master with ensuite, family bathroom boasting quality fixtures and fittings, and laundry to complete the package. Stairs lead up to the generous sized fourth bedroom/multi purpose room and a lovely outdoor balcony with a gorgeous treed outlook and water glimpses.
Additional features include two split systems, stone benchtops, walk in pantry, dishwasher, Miele under bench oven/ceramic cook top, Gas heater, a 3.1 kilowatt solar energy system, huge double shed, beautiful paved terrace amongst the delightful garden, ceiling fans
In addition, the property boasts double carport with remote control roller doors as well as a large shed providing ample room for car, boat or caravan storage.
Inspection will impress!

Description:
OPEN FOR INSPECTION CANCELLED - SATURDAY 30TH SEPTEMBER
A rare opportunity exists to acquire a 5 acre (approx.) lot of land only 5 minutes from Cowes, with impressive rural and native bush views abundant with wildlife - where the Wallaby roam.
The property features an over 40m2, architecturally designed and locally MB built Sandstone home which borders an ongoing farm whose cattle can be used to keep the 2 of the 3 paddocks manicured, mains water also supplied to these. If you wish to manage your own hobby farm, the property also comes with loading stockyard (high enough to take horses) and crush.
This magnificent home consists of 3 wings, the west wing promotes master with ensuite (large spa), his & hers walk in wardrobes & powder room which can be closed off to the adjoining living room. Open plan central dining/kitchen, all north facing with wrap around windows to capture the landscape, opening out to an expansive deck.
The crafted large timber kitchen with walk in pantry, massive island bench with stone bench tops is a cooks dream, with Black Butt timber flooring thoughout.
The eastern wing has three further bedrooms, one with semi ensuite and another powder room, rumpus room with own entry to the yard and a sink, a smaller covered deck, separate storage room, separate laundry & entry to the house from the double lock up garage. Side entry to the house from the garage entry takes you to the formal living room.
Whether you are looking for a unique lifestyle or a sea change, this is a wonderful opportunity in an exceptional location.
Extra features are:
• Solar hot water
• 20,000lt water tank
• Mains water and power
• Sewerage recycle system to water the gardens
• Reverse cycle heating and cooling
• Large under house storage area with lockable door
• Small pond in the garden

Description:
Bring Outdoor Living In!
Architect-designed, two-bedroom home plus study featuring high ceilings and an innovative floor plan which makes the most of the northern sun, creating a sense of light and space.
A north-oriented courtyard provides sun-filled private space sheltered from cooler southerly breezes, while large windows and bi-fold doors link the space to the rest of the home, flooding the surrounding rooms with light.
The home features ducted, reverse-cycle air-conditioning, generous storage, a large fully-fitted kitchen, remote control garage and a range of luxury inclusions.
Located in the environmentally-sensitive Seagrove residential estate, just 800 metres from Thompson Avenue in Cowes, this home is close to the beach, shops, restaurants and cafes.
Originally built as a display village, this home is to be incorporated into the Seagrove estate, with a planned service road connection to Seagroves road and walking path network. Just 50 metres away, a new park is planned around a stand of large Eucalypt trees. Beyond this, walking and cycle paths will connect to Seagroves more than eight acres of landscaped open space.
This property won't last, book your inspection today!

Description:
DESIGNER HOME OUTSTANDING LOCATION
This property has been designed by an award winning local architect with one of the best names in the industry.
Set in the pristine Shearwater estate with over 5 hectares of wetlands and parklands. Enjoy the dynamic combination of open spaces, natural environment complete with a thriving ecosystem and bustling wildlife.
Shearwater is located next to the Phillip Island Golf course, just a short drive to Cowes and 700m from Silverleaves beach.
This home was built to encompass the northern ambient sun that flows into the central open plan living/kitchen/dining.
This grand space is designed with high raked ceilings, hardwood timber floors large sliding doors overlooking the native gardens and semi alfresco decked area.
The premium kitchen is cleverly designed with stone bench tops, stainless steel appliances, large pot draws, glass window-splash back and an integrated butler's pantry.
Across the home, find a private study, 4 generous sized bedrooms complete with BIR's, Master room offers views over the native gardens, spacious walk in robe and a modern private ensuite.
The home is positioned well to allow side access to the large shed great for storing a boat or trailer and access to a private back yard perfect for a large vegetable garden.
Book your inspection today and see what this beautiful home has to offer.
